title: N Line - Weekday and Weekend Planned Service Changes
body: DAYS9:45 AM to 3 PM,  Mon to Fri,  Apr 17 - 21Manhattan-bound N trains are rerouted via the D from Stillwell Av to 36 St,  due to track replacement. Trains run express,  stopping at Bay 50 St,  Bay Pkwy,  62 St-New Utrecht Av,  and 9 Av. To 86 St,  Avenue U,  Kings Hwy,  Bay Pkwy,  20 Av,  18 Av,  Fort Hamilton Pkwy,  and 8 Av,  take the Manhattan-bound D or N to New Utrecht Av-62 St or 36 St and transfer to a Coney Island-bound D* or N. To 59 St,  take the Manhattan-bound D or N to 36 St and transfer to a Coney Island-bound D/N or Bay Ridge-bound R. title: 1, 2, 3, 5, 6, A, E, F, L, M Lines Š—– CANCELLATION of Weeknight Planned Service Changes
body: With the exception of the long-term service changes on the 6 and A routes,  all other planned service changes scheduled for overnight Jan 7 to 8 are cancelled.  Due to the overnight forecast of sub-freezing temperatures and windy weather conditions,  NYC Transit has placed into effect Winter Operations Plan No. 2.  The plan calls for the underground storage of subway trains and the cancellation of overnight maintenance work,  including FASTRACK.  The underground storage of trains protects them from harsh conditions and ensures that they will be available and ready for morning rush service.  FASTRACK operation was scheduled this week for the No. 6 Line between 125th Street and Hunts Point Avenue.  However,  its suspension means that subway customers will not have to transfer for shuttle buses and it will provide storage space overnight for idle No. 6 trains. Depending on the severity of weather,  regular subway service may be affected.  Click here for details of our Cold Weather Plan: htt                          1/7/15 1:57 PM             NYC
